SIMPLE: southern
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Southern
<hw>South"ern</hw> <pr>(?; 277)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[AS.
<ets>s⟦umac⟧⟦edh⟧ern</ets>. See <er>South</er>.]</ety> <def>Of or
pertaining to the south; situated in, or proceeding from, the south;
situated or proceeding toward the south.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Southern Cross</b></col> <fld>(Astron.)</fld>, <cd>a
constellation of the southern hemisphere containing several bright stars
so related in position as to resemble a cross.</cd> -- <col><b>Southern
Fish</b></col> <fld>(Astron.)</fld>, <cd>a constelation of the southern
hemisphere (<spn>Piscis Australis</spn>) containing the bright star
Fomalhaut.</cd> -- <col><b>Southern States</b></col> <fld>(U.S. Hist. &
Geog.)</fld>, <cd>the States of the American Union lying south of
Pennsylvania and the Ohio River, with Arkansas, Louisiana, and Texas.
Before the Civil War, Missouri also, being a slave State, was classed as
one of the Southern States.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Southern</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Southern
<hw>South"ern</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A Southerner.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Southerner</ent>⟦br⟧
